'''''Mitzi...Roarin' in the 20s''''' is a 1976 [[Emmy Award]] winning television special starring [[Mitzi Gaynor]].
==Overview== The [[variety show]] included [[music]] and [[comedy]] and guest starred [[Carl Reiner]], [[Linda Hopkins]] and [[Ken Berry]].<ref name="credits">[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0337682/fullcredits#cast IMDb - Full cast and crew for Mitzi... Roarin' in the 20's]</ref> It was produced by Jack Bean, Tom Biener and Harry Waterson; and directed by Brian Bartholomew and Keaton S. Walker.<ref name="credits"/>
==Awards== Costume designer [[Bob Mackie]] won an Emmy for "Outstanding Achievement in Costume Design for Music-Variety".<ref name="emmy">[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0337682/awards IMDb - Awards for Mitzi... Roarin' in the 20's]</ref> John Freschi won an Emmy for "Outstanding Achievement in Lighting Direction".<ref name="emmy"/>
