[[Image:Rocket Festival 06 Lizard flags.jpg|thumb|Lizard and Flags Rocket 2006]]
The Rocket Festival was a three-day festival of [[music]], [[circus]], [[performance art]] and [[sculpture]] set in [[Andalucia]] in southern [[Spain]] that was held in May 2005, 2006 and 2008.

The festival evolved from the [[free festival]] movement in the UK and inspired by events such as [[Glastonbury Festival]]  and [[Shambala festival|Shambala Festival]].

The organisers have a long history in the UK festival and free party scene from [[Stonehenge]] to [[Glastonbury Festival|Glastonbury]].<ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/bristol/content/articles/2008/05/16/spain_festival_feature.shtml</ref> The Rocket was conceived as a melting-pot of this alternative festival culture with the Spanish [[festival|fiesta]] spirit set in a rural location near Alhama de Granada, Andalucia.

==Rocket festivals==
* 29/04/2005 - 31/04/2005 in a rugged valley in the [[Sierra de Camorolos]] near [[Antequera]], 50&nbsp;km north of [[Málaga]] featuring [[Amparanoia]] and The [[Freestylers]]
* 18/05/2006 - 20/05/2006 at the Finca de Los Morales, near [[Alhama de Granada]], [[Granada]], [[Spain]] featuring [[Eskorzo]] and [[Dreadzone]]
* 16/05/2008 - 10/05/2008 at the same site as 2006 near [[Alhama de Granada]], [[Granada]], [[Spain]] featuring [[Coldcut]], [[Pendulum (drum and bass band)|Pendulum]], [[Evil Nine]], [[The Nextmen]], [[Muchachito Bombo Infierno]], and [[Los Delinqüentes]]

